<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06343017 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06343017 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  OPINION; US; PRESIDENT; HUMOR  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  YOU KNOW George Bush's unrehearsed, spontaneous conversations, where he ishooked up to the annual convention of the National Plumb Bob ManufacturersAssociation by satellite TV and answers questions from the audience?;   Wordarrives that the questions and answers are written out ahead of time by WhiteHouse flacks. It's a charade.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Perspective  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ANSWERS FOR ALL QUESTIONS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Points of View; Donald Kaul is a syndicated columnist.  </MEMO><TEXT>     Bush got caught the other day when he gave answer A to question B.;   Somuch for truth in government.;   We can look forward to the following pressconference:;   Q. Are you planning anything special for Mrs. Bush's birthday?;  A. We've just about decided to put her to sleep. It's sad and we hate to doit, but she is getting up in years and she's become terribly crotchety.;   Q.Have Millie the dog's recent antics put her out of favor?;   A. Absolutelynot. Never been more satisfied with a performance. Mistakes happen, but it'snot easy to be the White House watchdog.;   Q. Did you have any personalanimosity toward your chief of staff, John Sununu?;   A. Look, the man is anabsolute disgrace. The fact he even calls himself a Republican is an outrage.;  Q. David Duke has said that he is running in the primaries against you. Areyou worried about the threat he poses?;   A. You people are trying to drive awedge between us. Couldn't feel closer to him if he were my son. I lookforward to going on the campaign trail with him next year.;   Q. Is there anythought to dumping Dan Quayle?;   A. This president is in favor of affirmativeaction.;   Q. How do you feel giving the disadvantaged of our nation an equalopportunity to share in the American dream?;   A. It makes me sick to mystomach. I think it's a shame and a scandal. You'll never see it happen in myadministration, believe me.;   Q. What are your thoughts on a nationalcondom-distribution program?;   A. Well, I'm not real thrilled at the idea. Ithink the situation is a perfect argument for the death penalty.;   Q. WillieHorton is due for parole soon. Are you concerned about his being loose on thestreets again?;   A. I'm hoping we can go off someplace alone for the weekend,just the two of us, and talk about old times. There's nobody I'd rather spendtime with.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Donald Kaul column  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911208  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3P  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  397  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday, December 8, 199100343017,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>